Package: clx-sbcl
Version: 0.5.4
Revision: 1
Description: Low-level X11 client library for SBCL
License: BSD
Maintainer: Lars Rosengreen <lars@margay.org>

Depends: fink-lisp-manager, sbcl, x11
Build-Depends: x11-dev

Source: http://ftp.linux.org.uk/pub/lisp/sbcl/clx_%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: dbc1ea318cea3c5939988c15ce28a96b

SourceDirectory: clx_%v

Patch: %n.patch

CompileScript: echo "nothing to do"

InstallScript: <<
  find %b -type d -name CVS -depth -exec rm -rf {} \;
  find %b -type f -name .cvsignore -exec rm -f {} \;
  %p/lib/common-lisp/scripts/install sbcl clx %i
<<

DocFiles: LICENSE README

PreRmScript: %p/lib/common-lisp/scripts/clean sbcl clx
PostInstScript: %p/lib/common-lisp/scripts/compile sbcl clx

DescDetail: <<
CLX is the common lisp equivilent of Xlib for C.
<<

DescUsage: <<
Stilll a little rough around the edges :)

%p --> where your fink installation is located (ie /sw)

(require :asdf)
(pushnew #P"%p/lib/common-lisp/sbcl/systems/" 
         asdf:*central-registry*)
(asdf:oos 'asdf:load-op 'clx)
<<

Homepage: http://www.cliki.net/CLX

